The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Paeans to the poet

 The magical rhythm and lyrics of Tagore?s poetry and songs weave a spell of harmony over humanity. His compositions in melody and verse are manifestations of his ideal vision of a world united by peace, love and brotherhood. They also envisage man?s oneness with nature, through which, the poet believes, one can perceive the true beauty of life. On the occasion of Tagore?s birth anniversary, Bhavna Records and Cassettes presents, Kavi-Pranam, a programme featuring Tagore songs, readings, audio-plays and dance. Participants include Aginbha Bandyopadhyay, Abhirup Guha Thakurta, Anindya Majumdar, Indrani Bhattacharya, Urmimala and Jagannath Basu, Kaberi Gupta, Gopa Roy, Goutam Mitra, Chandrabali Rudra, Taslima Nasreen, Tejendra Narayan Majumdar, Dipak Rudra, Barin Roy, Rupankar, Monomoy, Riddhi and Devajit Bandyopadhyay, Pramita Mallick, Pabitra Sarkar, Papia Adhikari, Sraboni Sen, Manisha Murali Nair, Manoj Murali Nair and Manasi Mukherjee.

 Event: Kavi-Pranam, a programme of Tagore songs, verse, audio-plays and dance

 When: Today at 5.30 pm

 Where: Rabindra Sadan




